# ============================================================
# rules.nsp — NetSec Policy File
# NetSec Policy Compiler (NSPC) — Example Policy
# ============================================================

# --- Network Scanning Rules (translated to nmap) ---
SCAN TARGET 192.168.1.100 PORT 80,443 WITH SYN_STEALTH
SCAN TARGET 10.0.0.0/24 PORT 22 WITH VULN_SCAN
SCAN TARGET 172.16.0.5 PORT 21,22,23,80 WITH OS_DETECT
SCAN TARGET 192.168.1.1 PORT 80 WITH PING_SCAN

# --- Firewall Rules (translated to iptables) ---
BLOCK INBOUND FROM 10.0.0.5 PROTOCOL UDP PORT 53
ALLOW OUTBOUND TO 8.8.8.8 PROTOCOL TCP PORT 443
BLOCK INBOUND FROM 203.0.113.5 PROTOCOL TCP PORT 22
ALLOW OUTBOUND TO 1.1.1.1 PROTOCOL TCP PORT 80
